headline: Where Does Zoetis Stand After New Partnerships and a 10% Drop in 2025?
summary: If you’re holding Zoetis stock or thinking about jumping in, it’s hard not to notice the recent shifts in its performance. Over the last week, shares have nudged upward by 1.3%, and in the past month, they're up 3.0%. But take a step back and the picture grows more complex: Zoetis is still down 10.3% year-to-date and 17.9% over the last year. For a global leader in animal health, that’s quite a ride.
